note.p:
Pub. L. 112–99, § 1(b), Mar. 13, 2012, 126 Stat. 265, provided that: “Subsection (f) of section 701 of the Tariff Act of 1930 [19 U.S.C. 1671(f)], as added by subsection (a) of this section, applies to— “(1) all proceedings initiated under subtitle A of title VII of that Act (19 U.S.C. 1671 et seq.) on or after November 20, 2006;
“(2) all resulting actions by U.S. Customs and Border Protection; and
“(3) all civil actions, criminal proceedings, and other proceedings before a Federal court relating to proceedings referred to in paragraph (1) or actions referred to in paragraph (2).”
